===Definitions===
{{head|zh|hanzi}}

# {{lb|zh|literary}} [[omen]]; [[sign]]; [[portent]] {{gloss|subtle signs before an event occurs; incipient state}}
#* {{zh-x|體 盡 無窮，而 遊 無 朕。|His substance is infinite, and he wanders in the '''pathless''' (sign-less/trace-less).|ref=Zhuangzi}}
#* {{zh-x|鴻 災 起 無 朕。|Great disasters arise without '''warning signs'''.|ref=Lü Wen (Tang Dynasty)}}
# {{lb|zh|archaic}} [[I]]; [[me]]; [[my]] {{gloss|general first-person pronoun used by anyone regardless of status, pre-Qin Dynasty}}
#* {{zh-x|朕 皇考 曰 ^伯庸。|'''My''' deceased father was named Boyong.|ref=Lisao}}
#* {{zh-x|爾 無 不 信，朕 不 食言。|On no account disbelieve '''me''' - **I** will not go back on my word.|ref=Shangshu}}
# {{lb|zh|imperial}} [[I]]; [[my]]; [[We]] {{gloss|reserved for use by the [[emperor]] or [[empress dowager]] since the [[w:Qin Dynasty|Qin Dynasty]]}}
#: {{zh-x|朕 即 國家|{{w|L'État, c'est moi|'''I''' am the state}}}}
#* {{zh-x|天子 自稱 曰 朕。|The Son of Heaven refers to himself as '''{{lang|zh|朕}}'''.|ref=Shiji}}
#* {{zh-x|皇太后 詔 有司 曰：『……春秋 六十，未 見 皇孫，食 不 甘味，寢 不 安席，朕 甚 悼 焉。』|The Empress Dowager issued an edict to the officials: "...I am sixty years old, yet have seen no imperial grandson... '''I''' grieve greatly over this."|ref=Hanshu}}
# {{lb|zh|Cantonese}} {{alt form|zh|𠹻|tr=zam6|t=classifier for smells}}

====Usage notes====
* In modern Chinese slang, sense 3 may sometimes be used ironically and humorously to refer to oneself.

